text.section:
Subject to § 9-709 of this subtitle, a court may appoint the Division Director, deputy division director, or an examiner from the Division of Savings and Loan Associations as conservator if the court finds that a savings and loan association or related entity is:
In an impaired or insolvent condition;
In substantial violation of any law or regulation;
Concealing any of its assets or records or refusing to submit its records or affairs for inspection to an examiner or lawful agent or the Division Director;
Conducting an unsafe or unsound operation;
In violation of any final order;
In need of the appointment of a conservator in order to preserve the assets of the savings and loan association for the benefit of the depositors and creditors; or
Eligible for conservatorship under the provisions of Title 10 of this article.
